00:41:36,207 --> 00:41:41,207
Uh, so quite a few people did try to, uh, cross over, but not from my company.

541
00:41:41,207 --> 00:41:46,207
There were only two cases, I'll tell you about them briefly.

542
00:41:46,207 --> 00:41:51,207
For me it was out of the question, because if I had tried to cross over

543
00:41:51,207 --> 00:41:56,207
my mother and my brother would have been arrested immediately.

544
00:41:56,207 --> 00:42:00,686
My brother was still living in Berlin. He was.

545
00:42:00,686 --> 00:42:04,483
So that was out of the question for me.

546
00:42:04,483 --> 00:42:09,483
(clears throat) There was a first lieutenant, he was a first lieutenant in an intelligence unit.

547
00:42:09,483 --> 00:42:12,599
And, uh, he disappeared one day.

548
00:42:12,599 --> 00:42:17,599
Nobody, uh, gave it any thought, because I told you, the so-called comradeship was shit.

549
00:42:17,599 --> 00:42:22,599
It didn't exist at all. Everyone lived for themselves and...

550
00:42:22,599 --> 00:42:27,599
