605
00:46:41,994 --> 00:46:46,376
My grandfather came from Galicia or whatever.

606
00:46:46,376 --> 00:46:51,376
Emigrated to America because of the pogroms, got himself a little old horse, a, what do you call it?

607
00:46:51,376 --> 00:46:56,376
Uh. Uh. A wagon like that. Yes, a covered wagon. Yes, a covered wagon. Yes. Mhm.

608
00:46:56,376 --> 00:47:01,376
Packed the covered wagon full of pots, with, uh, anything that might be knives

609
00:47:01,376 --> 00:47:06,376
forks, uh, something that was interesting for Indians back then.

610
00:47:06,376 --> 00:47:11,376
And, uh, on the Indian reservation, my great-grandmother went into labor.

611
00:47:11,376 --> 00:47:14,589
And they brought her into a tent.

612
00:47:14,589 --> 00:47:19,589
And the Indian women were so great at that sort of thing, the indigenous people.

613
00:47:19,589 --> 00:47:24,589
A birth was a small thing. And they helped my grandmother, er, into life.

614
00:47:24,589 --> 00:47:29,589
